parties.raw_snippet:
THIS MARINE TRANSPORTATION AGREEMENT (this “Agreement”) is executed this 23rd day of December, 2003, by and between Martin
Operating Partnership L.P., a Delaware limited partnership (“Owner”), and Midstream Fuel Service LLC, an Alabama limited liability company
(“Charterer”),
parties.reasoning: The introductory paragraph explicitly states the parties by legal names and their roles (Owner and Charterer).

contract_type.raw_snippet:
in order to evidence the agreement of such parties with respect to Owner’s provision of marine transportation services with respect
to #2 fuel oil and high sulfur diesel on board its marine vessels under the following terms and conditions.
contract_type.reasoning: The core obligation is the Owner providing marine transportation services for fuel products. This is a transportation-focused services contract.

notice_period.raw_snippet:
This Agreement will automatically renew for successive one year terms
(each a “Renewal Term”, and together with the Initial Term, the “Term”), unless either Charterer or
Owner elects not to renew this Agreement by providing the other party with written notice of such
election 30 days prior to the expiration of the Initial Term or Renewal Term, as applicable, at which
point this Agreement will automatically terminate.
notice_period.reasoning: This clause sets the advance written notice required to prevent automatic renewal: 30 days prior to the expiration of the then-current term.

expiration_date.raw_snippet:
The initial term of this Agreement shall be for 3 years (the “Initial Term”) commencing on the date
first set forth above (the “Commencement Date”) and ending on the 3rd anniversary of the
Commencement Date.
expiration_date.reasoning: The agreement specifies a 3-year initial term ending on the 3rd anniversary of the Commencement Date.

renewal_term.reasoning: The agreement provides for automatic renewals in one-year increments.
